main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Proctor, Minnesota on 28 March 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as round and approximately the size of a baseball when observed from a distance., It had red and white flashing lights and produced a roaring sound., The observer noted an erratic flight path with frequent course changes., The object was seen for approximately 20 minutes around 11 PM., Many other people in Proctor reported similar sightings around the same time.
sighted object: round object with red and white flashing lights
